               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17670909-42-off251-c406" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-defend490 t17670909-42-off251 t17670909-42-verdict255"></join>
         
               <p>454. (L.) 
               <persName id="t17670909-42-defend490" type="defendantName">
                  Rebecca 
                  Salter 
               <interp inst="t17670909-42-defend490" type="surname" value="Salter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-defend490" type="given" value="Rebecca"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-defend490" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t17670909-42-off251" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-off251" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-off251" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing seven pewter plates, value 3 s 6 d.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17670909-42-victim492" type="victimName">
                     Richard 
                     Wethers 
                  <interp inst="t17670909-42-victim492" type="surname" value="Wethers"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-victim492" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-victim492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-off251 t17670909-42-victim492"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17670909-42-cd252" type="crimeDate">Aug 14</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-off251 t17670909-42-cd252"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670909-42-person493">
                  Richard 
                  Wethers 
               <interp inst="t17670909-42-person493" type="surname" value="Wethers"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person493" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person493" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t17670909-42-viclabel253" type="occupation">keep a <placeName id="t17670909-42-crimeloc254">public house in Cloth-fair</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-crimeloc254" type="placeName" value="public house in Cloth-fair"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-crimeloc254" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-off251 t17670909-42-crimeloc254"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-victim492 t17670909-42-viclabel253"></join>. On the 14th of August, when I came down in the morning, my wife told me she had lost a dozen plates; while my wife and I were talking, the prisoner came in, and was about two hours over a pennyworth of beer; I suspected her, and desired some neighbours in the house to take notice of her; after some time, they called to me, and let me know she was gone backwards; I met her coming out; she had two of my pewter plates under her apron; then upon charging her, she owned she had taken and sold eleven to Mrs. Pye in Aldersgate street; I went there; Mrs. Pye put a dozen before me, I swore to five of them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670909-42-person494">
                  Mary 
                  Pye 
               <interp inst="t17670909-42-person494" type="surname" value="Pye"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person494" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person494" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pewterer; I bought these five plates of the prisoner at the bar a month ago last Saturday; (produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I am not guilty.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17670909-42-person495">
                  John 
                  Cozens 
               <interp inst="t17670909-42-person495" type="surname" value="Cozens"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person495" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-person495" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I married the prisoner's sister; I always looked upon her to be very honest; her husband has used her very ill, and has now left her in distress</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17670909-42-verdict255" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-verdict255" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-verdict255" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17670909-42-punish256" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-punish256" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17670909-42-punish256" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670909-42-defend490 t17670909-42-punish256"></join>
               W
            </rs>.</p>
